* Remember that even though you failed to defeat a Boss, you still have some time to fight it again and finish the job.

* Using SUPER STRIKE will be the only way to defeat a Boss with a higher level.

* Rewards for Boss fights increase slowly while fighting Bosses on lower levels, but will gradually get better as you progress through the levels.

* After reaching one goal and claiming the reward, a new goal appears.

* The goals differ in objective, difficulty and reward.

* Quests are assignments given to hero by NPCs. * They lead the character through the game and allow valuable prizes to be won. * New quests are available after finishing the required quest, unlocking locations or reaching certain levels in the game. * Each quest can only be done once. * Given quest prizes must be claimed; they are not added automatically.

* Completing daily tasks is rewarded with points. * The number of points for each task can be seen in the task description. * Reaching certain numbers of task points is rewarded with prizes. * Tasks are reloaded daily, at 03:00 UTC.

* Stage list is a list of all stages in one location on one difficulty. * Passing all stages in a location unlocks the next new location. * Stages marked red are Boss Stages. * Boss Stages are harder, but there is a chance of getting a stage prize, visible on the stage icon. * Each stage can be finished with one, two or three stars. * To achieve a bigger amount of stars, a player needs to finish combat in shorter time (smaller number of turns). * After getting the required number of stars in a location, players can claim their prize. * There are two levels of difficulty. The higher difficulty is unlocked at level 18. * At each level of difficulty, map progress starts from zero and the rewards for combat and stars are different. * The number of battles you can fight at one stage is limited. * The Stage Battle Limit can be reset with gems. * This limit is separate for each stage of the game. * Skip battle feature is always available in the battles you have already won. * Using Auto loot requires 3 stars on a given stage.

* Chests are full of powerful Gear. * Every one in ten Eternal Chests Openings has a guaranteed Legendary(5*) Gear prize. * Chests are available for free: - Silver - every 10 minutes, 3 times a day - Golden - every 24 hours - Eternal - every 72 hours * Chests can be opened with a specific Chest Key. * Opening Chests with a Chest Key doesn't require any gems.

* Items in this shop can be purchased with gems only. 

* Item purchased remains available in the shop with no amount limit. 

* Premium shop inventory may change periodically.

* Shopping allows you to get craft materials, items and item parts. * The shop reloads every 3 hours. * Reloading partially or completely changes the shop inventory and restocks it back to full. * You reload the shop inventory by paying Gems . * Item prices and shop inventory may change during events.
* Spin to get rewards. * The first daily spin is free. * After the free spin, you can activate Tavern Spin with Spin Tokens and Gems.

* Craft to get rewards. * Getting the main prize may require finishing smaller crafts (sub-crafts), which are also awarded with prizes. * Completing a craft requires using materials (items, Gear, or Orbs) that meet the criteria listed in crafting requirements. * In the process, all items used for crafting are irretrievably lost, including currencies. * There are different types of crafting: multiple, one-time, regular and event. * There are few tabs that are always available and some that are just time-limited, like event crafts that may appear in a new tab. * In the Tokens tab you can turn not used gear into Craft Tokens which are used in other crafts. * The Keys tab allows you to craft Chest keys and Legendary Gear Shards. * In the Swap tab you can try to exchange Gear of a specific emblem into random Gear from that emblem. It is possible to get some gear as you put into the exchange. * Swaps requires Swap Tokens that can be crafted and additionally received from Scheme crafts. Note that not all emblem Gear is possible to get from Swap. * Scheme craft allows you to exchange Gear Scheme into random gear of a specific emblem. In addition, you receive Swap Tokens that can be used in the Swap tab.

* Dividing allows retrieving Eternium and other resources invested in upgrading and reforging Gear. * When dividing, you can decide if you want to get back the Gear itself or a number of Parts of that Gear. * Gear of certain high qualities, like Artifacts and above, cannot be divided into Parts. * If the item was Boosted, materials used to boost it are also retrieved from the Dividing process. * Dividing requires a Divide Token. * There are 3 types of Divide Tokens: - Lesser Divide Token - Retrieves 80% of the materials used in upgrading (eternium, reforge, empowering stone) - Superior Divide Token - Retrieves 95% of the materials used in upgrading (eternium, reforge, empowering stone) - Awaken Divide Token - Retrieves 95% of the materials used in upgrading (eternium, reforge, empowering stone) - Awaken Divide Token - Divides Artifacts into Legendary Craft Tokens, which can be used in the Awaken - Awaken Divide Token - Retrieves 20% used gears, converting them into Legendary Craft Tokens

* Smelt useless items and turn them into Eternium . * Smelted items are irreversibly destroyed. * You cannot smelt items that have been upgraded or boosted. * The amount of Eternium received for an item depends on the item's quality. * Items of high quality (rare and higher) have to be added to smelt manually.

* The bank generates a passive income of Gold . * The bank can only hold a limited amount of gold. When this amount is reached, the income of gold no longer increases. * Gold claiming is free of charge and unlimited. * Both passive income and bank gold limit increase with each level gained by your character.

* You can send your ship on a voyage - when it comes back you will be awarded Eternium , Gold and a Barrel. * You can only have one active voyage at a time. * Being on a voyage doesn't block any other game activities. * You will be awarded an additional prize for finishing all voyages on the list. * The list of voyages reloads every 4 hours. * The moment the list of voyages reloads, all unfinished voyages from the previous list are deleted - except the one that is currently active. * All voyages can be finished instantly by paying a given number of gems . * After finishing all your voyages you can pay gems to immediately load a new list. * You can trade Barrels you earned on Voyages in Trade Shop in the City.

* Place Gear in Collections to activate the bonuses of equipped gear and increase their statistics. * Each item inserted into the Collection increases the statistics of your Hero, depending on the slot into which it was docked. * If the item in the Collection slot has a level higher than 1, the Collection will only take the base stats of this item into consideration (Level 1, without Reforge stats). Instead, the only additional stats considered in the Collection slots are stats from Boosts. * Slots may be improved so that they give a higher statistic to items docked in them. * Unlocking and upgrading slots requires Collection Scrolls. * Collection I and II require different types of Scrolls.

* Parts tab contains parts of Gear and Gear Shards you own. * After collecting a required number of Parts, you can merge them into a specific Gear. * After collecting a required number of Gear Shards you can merge them into random Gear. * You can check the list of possible loots from Gear Shards by tapping [...] icon on the Shard's pop-up. * Parts can be acquired from extracting, battle, quests, tavern spins and events. * Items used in the process of dividing may be returned as Parts.

* Allows the exchange of an already docked Orb for a different one.

* Lists only Orbs of the same type as the one you are trying to exchange.

* You can choose between two views: one shows currently worn Orbs, the other shows all the Orbs you have.

* The little icon next to the Orb shows which Gear the Orb is currently docked in.

* You may use other Orbs or special Essences to enhance Orbs. * Orbs and Essences used in the process of enhancing are irreversibly destroyed. * Enhancing increases an Orb's statistics by the given percentage. * Each new level of enhancing requires more Orbs or Essences. * Higher quality Orbs and Essences (e.g. epic or legendary) are more efficient - you will need less of them to gain results. * There are three separate types of Essences, each for different types of Orbs (Health, Defense, Attack/Magic).

* Upgrading consumes Gold to increase an Orbs statistics.

* The maximum level of an Orb's upgrade is equal to your Hero level.

* The higher the level, the more gold is required for upgrading.

* The gold you've spent on the Orb upgrade is non-recoverable.

* Each docked Orb increases one of your Hero's statistic by its own statistics. * Orbs can be docked in Gear slots. Each Gear has 3 Orb slots to choose from, depending on the Orb type. * There are three types of Orbs: - Health - Attack/Magic - Defense * Each slot can be filled with only one Orb. * Orb stats can be increased by upgrading or enhancing. * You can get new Orbs from: crafting, quests and events.

* Each active bonus increases Gear statistic by the given percentage. * Each bonus requires a Gear or Orb listed in the bonus description. * To activate a bonus, the required item must be either worn by your Hero or put in one of the Collections. * Only Orbs docked in the same slot as the item are taken into account when measuring this particular item's bonus. * You need to have 2 out of the 3 listed Gear Equipped or in your Collections to activate a Gear's bonus, and 1 out of the 2 Orbs docked to activate the Orb bonus. * Full list of bonuses for items currently worn by your character can be found in the Collection bookmark.

* List of all unused Gears fitting the given slot. * Allows quick exchange of items. * Items that are part of a Collection are not on the list. * If you want to wear these items, you must remove them from the Collection first. * You can long-press an item icon to see its details.

* Boosting requires an identical item as the one you want to boost (or enough parts to combine them into the said item) and it will raise the stats of your item by the percentage given. * You can only boost with items that have not been upgraded or boosted before. * The item used for boosting will be destroyed in the process. * The maximum boost level of an item is limited to: - 3 for common gears - 5 for uncommon gears - 10 for rare gears - 15 for epic gears - 20 for legendary gears * You can use Divide to retrieve items previously consumed in the boosting process.

* Upgrading consumes your Eternium and levels up a Gear's stats. * The maximum level of a Gear upgrade depends on item quality: * Common - 20 level * Uncommon - 40 level * Rare - 60 level * Epic - 80 level * Legendary - 100 level * - Legendary + - 120 level * - 140 level * - 160 level * The higher the level, the more Eternium and Gold is required for upgrading. * During an upgrade, the item gains the number of stat points equal to its potential. * You can use Dividing to get back most of the Eternium invested in upgrading an item. * Upgrading gear will also grant Reforge Points * After 100, 120 and 140 level you need to additionally Empower gear to enable the further upgrades.

* All the items that your character is wearing increases your statistics.

* An item will increase your character's statistics by the number of points it holds.

* You can level up any item's statistics by [b]boosting[/b] or [b]upgrading[/b] it.

* Boosting causes an increase in the item's potential and statistics.

* The higher the [b]potential[/b] of an item, the more its statistics grow with each upgrade.

* Statistics displayed on the item are a summary of the item's base stats, upgrade, boosts and bonuses.

* The more [b]stars[/b] an item has, the better it is.

* You can raise your item statistics even higher by simultaneously wearing items linked with the same bonus.

* You can get new items from chests, crafting, quests, events or from the shop.

'Hero smiled while entering Miremoon, 
He will be a bag of bones pretty soon"
Ah, Wastelands! They bring memories back. Sweet memories of carnage, guts and blood.
Sometimes when you fight in the same location for the second time it feels EVEN BETTER. And sometimes not.
Druids say that if you insult the Oak, it will turn you into a dried up leaf. So try fighting in a respectful manner.
This quest was supposed to be hard...So I wrote some hate mail to all the monsters before this battle. It will make them extra angry.
I can see how eager you are to fight evil, so I've woken up some monsters in those ruins for you.
What if I told you that you can go through this hassle again, but with a much bigger possibility of dying? Excited?
This is dangerous, yes. But what do you expect the deadly road to glory to look like? Easy and sunny?
This place use to be somewhat popular with mages. And mages are absentminded. They must have left something behind.
I heard of a caravan being trapped in sandstorm just around here. People run away, but beasts are still guarding the goods. Shall we explore?
Long ago, these ruins used to be the most beautiful and developed city in Valia. Respect that, and the spirit of this place will become your ally.
Looting in water is very similar to looting on land. All you need is big lung capacity and no respect for the dead.
This place has always been known for it's peace and beauty. Now it's also known for being monster infested and deadly. Tourism has never been better!
Even the most inbred Orc knows that it's forbidden to spill blood in these areas. But these monsters give us no choice, so...
This route is dangerous, so there is a lot of corpses with loot on them here... Wait, are you thinking what I'm thinking?
Would you mind fighting here for me in this extremely dangerous jungle filled with enemies?
Time for your body building exercise! Let's strengthen those muscles by cutting off some heads. Chop chop!
I heard of a caravan being trapped just around here. People run away, but beasts are still guarding the goods.Try looting a lost item from them.
This jungle smells like my aunt Bulba. She was a lovely woman but hated baths.
Jungle may be daunting and wicked but just think of those war treasures...
My perfect birthday gift? Just a warm smile from my child...haha, NOT. Loot, obviously. No smile can beat a 24-carat gold chain!
I love our little adventure. I find myself a bottle of grog, watch you fight and loot. It's very relaxing.
What's better than slaying endless beasts? Slaying beasts and searching for loot, of course.
Sometimes I get so into looting that I accidentally plunder my own treasures. True story.
Sometimes I wonder if loot is the most important thing in my life... And the answer is always a solid and happy 'YES'.
Nobody asks WHY these monsters are so angry. Maybe we should try to understand them, know more about their upbringing...Just kidding. BLOOD BAAAATH!!!
When lava cools rapidly it creates basalt. And when your gear cools rapidly it creates SWAG.
I don't always assign looting expeditions with monsters, but when I do, I make sure they are extremely dangerous.
This place deserved to be invaded by evil. I tried their wine and it was horrible.
I used to be an adventurer like you. Then I took a break and now my knees are fine. Think about it.
There is no such thing as too much loot, however you can have one battle too many...
Hey hey, no sleeping! I know you feel great about your skills but stay alert!
Think of it that way - if you don't kill them, age will. So it's almost like speeding up time.
I used to be worried about you... Now that I see how happy killing monsters makes you, I feel so much calmer. You were born to do this job.
This used to be an infamous hideout for all the Valian outcasts...As evil spread, more and more of these men would join the dark forces. Now most of them are demons.
Experience is important but exercisers is vital. Time for your training!
I once defeated 10 monsters like this with one single fireball. It got me fame, glory and second degree burns.
If I told you there are 9 very valuable items in this deadly abyss, would you jump? If you need a little push, I am here.
When people ask me what is the secret to my combat technique, I always say the same thing: EMBRACE THE KILLING. And the rest will happen naturally.

I'm sorry, there won't be any milk and cookies on this adventure. I just wanted to trick you into clicking on this quest.
AND I SUCCEEDED HA HA HA!
This is a very dark place... I don't mean metaphorically, I mean literally I CAN'T SEE A DAMN THING!
The creature you meet at the end of this battle has fed on fear for such a long time that's it grown very strong and very cruel. Good luck, you will need it.
I'll be damned, you hurl those fireballs as if you were spitting cherry pits! You don't need luck during this quest - those monsters do!
One day we will come back here and have a proper beach holiday... Or I can scatter your ashes here. What do you say about that?
What's the best way to make a monster angry? Ignore him. Monsters love attention.
I once knew a daredevil who claimed he could walk through this place while juggling 10 balls in his hands. I don't know how far he got; the only thing left of him was 10 balls and 2 eyeballs, hehe.
Nothing better after a fight in a sea storm than a warm cup of cocoa and some sweet loot to collect.
Nothing makes heroes fight as viciously as such freezing wind.
Why would anybody invade a place with such weather! Yet another reason to think monsters are stupid.
This is not an easy task, but hero's life is not suppose to be easy.
{NPC.3} tells you to rely on your instincts - I think that during fighting monsters might as well rely on your smell.
When your eyes fail you and you feel disoriented, try using your instincts. They never lie.
Your job is to kill all the crazy demons on our way. My job is to watch and sometimes laugh.
Sometimes I prefer to fight in gloomy locations, these aesthetics go so much better with slaughter.
You’ve been honing your crafting skills for a while - I think you’re ready to create me a masterpiece. It’s going to be Legendary!
Some quest are more pleasant than others. Like this one.
Some say things you create yourself hold the biggest value...
I have three huge chests filled with loot waiting to be delivered, all I need is a willing captain. Will you help me out here?
We have a very valuable cargo that needs to be delivered to Grey Valley. These are treacherous waters, so make sure that the ship reaches destination safely.
There have been rumours of a sea creature destroying ships and killing innocent men... I need you to sail there and check the area for anything blood-lusting.
I don't care if you've never sailed before. It's high time you learned!
I need some magical ingredients from the High Elves of Driannon. They live on a small island in the middle of the ocean. Will you please help me?
Travelling broadens the mind...aaand it's a great way to get some cash and Eternium.
I was never a fan fighting gloves myself, I prefer to fight with bare hands. But you should probably protect your soft, gentle frame with something more sturdy, hahah!
What would you say if I asked you to get me something from a very dangerous forest? Nothing? Okay, the job is yours.

A hero has to be in great shape. Growing hero power is the best sign of your progress and hard work.
Experience is important but exercises are vital. Time for your training, time to progress!
I know that {NPC.4} always says that faith doesn't win you battles, but what about believing in YOURSELF?
I can see you have been skipping Leg Day. Time to work out!
People toss the word "epic" way too much these days. Craft me an epic token - now that's a truly epic deed! Chop chop!
You know what would make me happy today? A golden key and a butter bun. I already have the bun, all I am missing is the key. Some help, maybe?
Time for you to show off your crafting skills. This is delicate work - I warn you.
Would you have time to craft one silver key for your favourite blacksmith? I bet you would.
If you make an uncommon item for me, I promise to say good things about you to Holger. Deal?
If only I could give you one legit reason not to spend gems...But I won't, because spending gems is amazing and fills my heart with joy.
The title of this quest is basically my second name. How about you? Let's see if we have anything in common, hero.
As a hero, sometimes you benefit from weird things. Like killing someone or spending gems.
If only I could give you one legit reason not to spend gems...But I won't, because spending gems is amazing and fills my heart with joy.
How about making that cash flow and eyes sparkle? Start spending!
Gems are like wine. Using a lot of them at once will make you giggle.
Rules are simple - you open up an eternal chest and fill an eternal happiness. So? Let's get happy!
Reaching level 20 will taste so much better with that giftbox Holger and I prepared for you. Enjoy it!
Another scary mission of opening a giftbox? I can only hope you won't get spoiled completely because of those.
You will be rewarded for opening a reward. If that's not a luxurious lifestyle, I don't know what is.
Here, have those. Maybe you will find them useful...You can call it a welcome present.
Dividing requires as much skill as fighting. Let's see if you are equally talented in this matter.

Whenever life gets you down, use one of these little babies. 
They are as powerful as they are delicious.
No hero became great without a substantial amount of barrels in his inventory. Everybody knows that.
You may sacrifice unused Orbs to enhance the power of others.
Docking Orbs in slots allows you to wield their power. Try it now.
To truly know the potential of an Orb you need to level it up regularly.
Perseverance is hero's second nature. That's why I want you to upgrade your armor 25 times.
How many chests one needs to open, to fill the void in his heart...Sometimes just one.
I knew you were a gambler the first moment I saw you.
Have you ever had a key made entirely out of magic? Well, seems like your time is now.
Whoever said money can't buy happiness never visited my shop.
This time, instead of killing barbaric beasts, I need you to create a key for me. Can you do it?
Old Elven saying goes: real hero sharpens the blade in his sleep. Remember - your gear requires constant attention.
If I was younger I would deal with Wasteland monsters myself. But I'm not, so...
I don't suppose you want to fight some extremely dangerous opponents now? If so, follow me.
All you see is graves and all I see is POSSIBILITY. Now tell me, how do you feel about opening a coffin or two?
Citadel used to be great. Sunny, happy, full of laughter... I'm joking. It was always horrible. But it doesn't mean we can abandon it.
Do you like digging in sand? Because this quest requires a lot of it.
I've had it with this desert! Kill those creatures and let's go somewhere damp and wet for a change.

I've already asked a few people to get some trinkets from Bushtrap and they never came back...Maybe you want to try?
Beautiful oasis in the middle of a deadly desert... Throw me into goblin mine if that doesn't sound very much like a trap.
Don't think about the ethics of this too much. You are a hero, not a philosopher, right?
